Name: 1_this_the_it_to
Representative_Docs: ['I think this needs a major rework: This code is not using ZenML materializers anymore and instead simply uses pickle for everything. If that was a good solution, instead of doing all this chunking we could just tell people to pickle the whole collection.', "Honeslty i don't think it is a good idea to enable it by default to all toolsets even if there wasn't trnasformer configure for it. Can you give an example for global transformer that you think we would like to enable on all toolsets?", 'You\'re absolutely right - the "0x" every 16 bytes was confusing and created output like [CODE] which looked like multiple hex numbers. I\'ve removed that logic in commit ec5efcc. Now it shows a clean continuous hex string like [CODE]. This hex format is only for display of truly unsupported data types with raw_data (not the low precision types which use int32_data). It\'s not meant to be parseable - just for inspection when the printer encounters an unknown data type.']
